text:
Mill Lane, east side, north of Ave. N. This house if standing would now (1936) be in front of 1597 East 53rd Street. This house, occupied by S. Van Dyke in 1835 and N. Van Dyke as late as 1873 was burned in 1922. A small frame building at 1597 is probably a part of the original home of one of the out buildings converted into a house.

1922.

Eugene L. Armbruster collection.
